      A friend in need is a friend indeed. Zeal without knowledge is the sister of folly Admiration is the daughter of ignorance  Gluttony kills more than the sword  The best throw of the dice is to throw them away 
      A drowning man will clutch at straws. A wise son brings joy to his father,but a foolish son grief to his mother. Dead men tell no tales To listen is to learn, and to understand is to inspire.. Things can only get better
    
    
      First come, first served  Do not wear out your welcome Discretion is the better part of valourHappy the bride who.. gets all the presents.
      Fight fire with fire Time and tide wait for no man Barking dogs seldom bite There's a black sheep in every flock. Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets. Better to meet a bear robbed of her cubs than a fool in his folly An ounce of practice is worth a pound of precept  
    
  
  When the student is ready, the master will appear  One mans meat is another mans poison! Confession is good for the soulThe man who removes a mountain begins by carrying away small stones Loving life is living life to the fullest Still waters run deep A ruler who oppresses the poor is like a driving rain that leaves no crops. Wedkey dress e pickney till he spoil.	 as wrinkled as an elephant's hide A fool at forty is a fool indeed. A helping hand is no farther than at the end of your sleeve.  Different strokes for different folk
